{"title_page": "List of French serial killers", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Dynamic list}}\n\nA [[serial killer]] is typically a person who [[murder]]s three or more people, with the murders taking place over more than a month and including a significant period of time between them.<ref>{{cite book|authors = Ronald M. Holmes, Stephen T. Holmes|title = Contemporary Perspectives on Serial Murder | publisher = [[SAGE Publications]] | year = 1998 | page = 1 | accessdate = June 15, 2016 |isbn = 0761914218| url = https://books.google.com/books?id=0yfoJz6jHwkC&pg=PA1|quote=Serial murder is the killing of three or more people over a period of more than 30 days, with a significant cooling-off period between the murders [...] The baseline number of three victims appears to be most common among those who are the academic authorities in the field. The time frame also appears to be an agreed-upon component of the definition.}}</ref>{{sfn|Burkhalter Chmelir|2003|p=1}} The [[Federal Bureau of Investigation]] (FBI) defines serial killing as \"a series of two or more murders, committed as separate events, usually, but not always, by one offender acting alone\".{{sfn|Burkhalter Chmelir|2003|p=1}}{{sfn|Morton|2005|p=4, 9}}\n\n==Identified serial killers==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!width=\"200px\"|Name!!width=\"100px\"|Years active!!data-sort-type=\"number\"|Proven victims!!data-sort-type=\"number\"|Possible victims!!Status!!Notes!!Ref\n|-\n| [[Vincenzo Aiutino|Aiutino, Vincenzo]]\n| 1991\u20131992\n| 3\n| 3\n| Sentenced to life imprisonment\n| Known as \"The Man with the Fifty Affairs\"; Swiss who raped and strangled three women between 1991 and 1992 in [[Meurthe-et-Moselle]]\n| <ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.estrepublicain.fr/actualite/2013/09/10/le-tueur-de-femmes-du-pays-haut |title=Vincenzo Aiutino, le tueur de femmes du pays haut |trans-title=Vincenzo Aiutino, the country's top killer of women |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=10 September 2013 |newspaper=[[L'Est R\u00e9publicain]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Patrice Al\u00e8gre|Al\u00e8gre, Patrice]]\n| 1989\u20131997\n| 5\n| 5+\n| Sentenced to life imprisonment\n| Raped and strangled women in [[Toulouse]] and [[Paris]]; his case caused accusations of a police cover-up\n| <ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/societe/justice/l-homme-qui-aimait-tuer-les-femmes_494034.html |title=L'homme qui aimait tuer les femmes |trans-title=The man who loved to kill women |first=Marie |last=Huret |date=7 February 2002 |magazine=[[L'Express]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Madame de Brinvilliers]]\n| 1666\u20131670\n| 3\n| 3\n| Executed 1676\n| Aristocrat who poisoned her father and two brothers\n| <ref>{{Cite book |url=http://www.intratext.com/IXT/ENG1175/_INDEX.HTM |title=The Marquise de Brinvilliers |first=Alexandre |last=Dumas |author-link=Alexandre Dumas |date=1850s |location=Paris |publisher=Marpon et Flammarion |via=IntraText CT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Brinvilliers, Marie Madeleine Marguerite d'Aubray, Marquise de |volume=4 |page=572}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Jean-Charles-Alphonse Avinain|Avinain, Jean-Charles-Alphonse]]\n| 1867\n| 2\n| 2\n| Executed 1867\n| Known as \"The Terror of [[Gonesse]]\"; butcher who killed two people in robberies\n| <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.criminocorpus.cnrs.fr/biblio/v3/b1.php?rech=avan&tt=&titre=&auteur=&plan=&personne=&quand=&lieu=&publi=&annee=&parpage=&oper1=&oper2=&oper3=&oper4=&oper5=&oper6=&histo=&atri=&dtri=&offset=16801&nbmax=100 |title=Cour d'assises of Seine. The butcher of Avinain |website=Criminocorpus |language=fr |accessdate=12 January 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061117130149/http://www.criminocorpus.cnrs.fr/biblio/v3/b1.php?rech=avan |archive-date=17 November 2006}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Marcel Barbeault|Barbeault, Marcel]]\n| 1969\u20131976\n| 8\n| 8\n| Sentenced to life impri