ate = June 15, 2016 |isbn = 0761914218| url = https://books.google.com/books?id=0yfoJz6jHwkC&pg=PA1|quote=Serial murder is the killing of three or more people over a period of more than 30 days, with a significant cooling-off period between the murders [...] The baseline number of three victims appears to be most common among those who are the academic authorities in the field. The time frame also appears to be an agreed-upon component of the definition.}}</ref>{{sfn|Burkhalter Chmelir|2003|p=1}} The [[Federal Bureau of Investigation]] (FBI) defines serial killing as \"a series of two or more murders, committed as separate events, usually, but not always, by one offender acting alone\".{{sfn|Burkhalter Chmelir|2003|p=1}}{{sfn|Morton|2005|p=4, 9}}\n\n==Identified serial killers==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!width=\"200px\"|Name!!width=\"100px\"|Years active!!data-sort-type=\"number\"|Proven victims!!data-sort-type=\"number\"|Possible victims!!Status!!Notes!!Ref\n|-\n| [[Vincenzo Aiutino|Aiutino, Vincenzo]]\n| 1991\u20131992\n| 3\n| 3\n| Sentenced to life imprisonment\n| Known as \"The Man with the Fifty Affairs\"; Swiss who raped and strangled three women between 1991 and 1992 in [[Meurthe-et-Moselle]]\n| <ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.estrepublicain.fr/actualite/2013/09/10/le-tueur-de-femmes-du-pays-haut |title=Vincenzo Aiutino, le tueur de femmes du pays haut |trans-title=Vincenzo Aiutino, the country's top killer of women |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=10 September 2013 |newspaper=[[L'Est R\u00e9publicain]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Patrice Al\u00e8gre|Al\u00e8gre, Patrice]]\n| 1989\u20131997\n| 5\n| 5+\n| Sentenced to life imprisonment\n| Raped and strangled women in [[Toulouse]] and [[Paris]]; his case caused accusations of a police cover-up\n| <ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/societe/justice/l-homme-qui-aimait-tuer-les-femmes_494034.html |title=L'homme qui aimait tuer les f